{"questionId":"22682","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In a city, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of people have blue eyes. If someone has blue eyes, the probability that they&nbsp;also have fair hair is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>58</mn><mo>%</mo></math>. This information is represented in the following tree diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/019743f2b8de67f003d3dd307df98bfc4b329e42.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression, in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>, for the probability of a person not having blue eyes&nbsp;<strong>and</strong> having fair hair.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>∩</mo><mi>F</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22682","referenceCode":"21N.1.SL.TZ0.11b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an expression, in terms of b, for the probability of a person not having blue eyes and having fair hair.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}